{
  "text": "Our main tool in the proofs, in addition to Lemmas 2.2 and 2.5 is Lemma 2.7 below, proved in [CITATION_1] . This lemma can be considered as a strengthened variant of the standard regularity lemma. This variant has two advantages. The first advantage is obtaining a regular partition in which all pairs are regular, where -roughly speaking -we compromise on the densities of the edges sets and consider only an induced subgraph of our graph which represents well the whole graph. The second advantage of this version is that one can define \u03b5 as a function of the size of the partition, rather than having to use a fixed \u03b5 as in Lemma 2.4. We denote such functions by E throughout the paper. ",
  "correct_citation": {
